<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="ug.reference-guide.sending.PlainSocketSender" version="8.0">
   <title>PlainSocketSender</title>
   <para>The sender uses a socket to send the message to and receive a response from.</para>
   <para>The target of the sender is a socket in a form of "&lt;host&gt;:&lt;port&gt;"</para>
   <example>
      <title>An example of PlainSocketSender configuration</title>
      <programlisting language="xml" linenumbering="numbered" startinglinenumber="1"><![CDATA[   <sender class="PlainSocketSender">
      <target>127.0.0.1:12345</target>
   </sender>]]></programlisting>
   </example>
</section>
